<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; DT 466E, DT 466, 530, 530E, and HT 530 Diesel Engines - Water Pump and Thermostat -
        Remove - Coolant Filter (If Equipped)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s210011002.4" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
        <title>Coolant Filter (If Equipped)</title>
        <para id="s210011002.4.1">The coolant filter must be removed prior to mounting engine on a stand.</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Relieve cooling system pressure by removing deaerating tank cap, if not already removed.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Close manual shutoff valve on coolant filter header by turning handle clockwise. In closed
                position, handle will be pointing straight up.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f210011006" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8043.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Close manual shutoff valve</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove coolant filter with a filter wrench or strap wrench. Filter is located on
                rear right side of front cover.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f210011007" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8624.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Remove coolant filter</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove three coolant filter header mounting bolts. Remove coolant filter header
                and discard seal and O-ring.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f210011008" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8613.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Remove coolant filter header</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Coolant filter header with manual shutoff valve has no serviceable components. If damaged or
                    leaking, replace entire filter header.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f210011009" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8612.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Coolant filter header seal and O-ring</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">O-ring</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
